[30;1m205 | [0m[35mBy default, it tries to use `md5sum` or equivalent.[0m
[30;1m206 | [0m[35mThe hash function can be manually switched by setting the `HASH` variable.[0m
[30;1m207 | [0m[35mFor example : `make HASH=xxhsum`[0m
[30;1m208 | [0m[35mThe hash function needs to generate at least 64-bit using hexadecimal format.[0m
[30;1m209 | [0m[35mWhen no hash function is found,[0m
[30;1m210 | [0m[35mthe Makefile just generates all object files into the same default directory,[0m
[30;1m211 | [0m[35mirrespective of compilation flags.[0m
